    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! Honestly, I\u2019m a little sad to see this one go, but it\u2019s time for a new home. This car is an absolute dream\u2014it looks and drives like it just rolled off the lot! I\u2019ve babied it since day one, keeping it in pristine, showroom condition inside and out. If you\u2019re looking for something that feels brand new without the full dealership price tag, this beauty is definitely the one for you. Come take it for a spin, you're going to love it!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit is mechanically superlative, boasting a factory-spec 8,000 RPM redline enabled by individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring precise torque distribution. This example has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement. The suspension geometry remains true with original bushings and dampening characteristics intact. Finished in Laguna Seca Blue with a pristine Nappa leather interior, this vehicle offers a pure, analog driving experience with zero mechanical compromises.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Single owner. Garage kept. Original paint. No scratches. Clean title. Full maintenance records included.",
      "price": 43500.0,
